# 🔍 DECO-HUB CRM — COMPLETE PROJECT AUDIT REPORT

**Audit Date:** 2026-03-04  
**Auditor Role:** Senior Software Architect & Security Auditor  
**Project Stack:** React 18 + Vite (Frontend), Express 5 + Prisma 5 (Backend), PostgreSQL (Database)  
**Environment:** Development/Staging → Production  

---

## 1. 📋 Executive Summary

The Deco-Hub CRM is a reasonably functional internal business tool for a blinds/curtains company, covering inquiries, selections, calculations, quotations, catalogs, attendance, and a kanban pipeline. The application demonstrates solid functional breadth — however, it carries **several critical security and structural risks** that must be resolved before production deployment.

**Overall Risk Score: `7.5 / 10` (HIGH)**  
> This score reflects serious security gaps (plaintext credentials in .env, open CORS, weak JWT secret, no rate limiting, no input validation, Supabase dead code) and significant architectural flaws (monolithic 3700-line backend file, no error code consistency, no pagination on large endpoints). These are not hypothetical risks; in production with real users and real financial data, they are exploitable.

---

## 2. 🏛️ Project Architecture Overview

```
deco-hub-crm/
├── src/                          ← React + Vite Frontend
│   ├── App.tsx                   ← Root router (315 lines)
│   ├── contexts/AuthContext.tsx  ← JWT Auth state
│   ├── lib/api.ts                ← Axios instance
│   ├── integrations/supabase/   ← ⚠️ DEAD CODE — Supabase not used
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── ProtectedRoute.tsx    ← Role-based route guard
│   │   └── layout/Sidebar.tsx   ← Navigation sidebar
│   └── pages/                   ← 14 feature page modules
│
└── server/
    ├── src/index.ts              ← ⚠️ MONOLITH: 3,713 lines, ALL routes
    ├── src/middleware/
    │   └── authMiddleware.ts     ← JWT verify + role check
    └── prisma/
        ├── schema.prisma         ← 866 lines, 30+ models
        └── seed.ts               ← Default superadmin seeder
```

**Architecture Verdict:** The backend is a **"God File" monolith**. All 80+ API routes live in a single 3,713-line [index.ts](file:///d:/deco-hub-crm/server/src/index.ts). This is an architectural anti-pattern that makes maintenance, testing, and debugging extremely difficult at scale.

