### 3.2 Duplicate Route Registration

**File:** [server/src/index.ts](file:///d:/deco-hub-crm/server/src/index.ts)  
**Lines:** 93–115 and 366–377

`POST /api/companies` is registered **twice** — once without a role guard (line 93) and once with [requireRole(['super_admin', 'admin_hr'])](file:///d:/deco-hub-crm/server/src/middleware/authMiddleware.ts#21-29) (line 366). In Express 5, the **first matching route wins**, meaning the unguarded one at line 93 takes priority.

```typescript
// Line 93 — NO role guard — this one wins!
app.post('/api/companies', authenticateToken, async (req: any, res) => { ... });

// Line 366 — Role guard — NEVER reached
app.post('/api/companies', authenticateToken, requireRole(['super_admin', 'admin_hr']), async ...
```

**Impact:** Any authenticated user can create companies, bypassing role restrictions.

### 3.3 Route Order Conflict — quotations

**File:** [server/src/index.ts](file:///d:/deco-hub-crm/server/src/index.ts) — Lines 2699 and 2816

The route `GET /api/quotations/pipeline/board` (line 3471) is registered **after** `GET /api/quotations/:id` (line 3094). Express will match `/api/quotations/pipeline` as `{ id: "pipeline" }` if the order is wrong. Verify ordering is correct (it appears it is in this file, but the route `GET /api/quotations/preview/:selectionId` on line 2699 shares a prefix conflict with `GET /api/quotations/:id` — these need careful ordering).

