## 13. 🎯 Risk Score Summary

| Category | Score | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| Authentication Security | 4/10 | Weak secret, localStorage JWT, no rate limit |
| Authorization / RBAC | 5/10 | Partial guards; delete/update holes exist |
| Data Validation | 3/10 | No input validation anywhere |
| CORS & External Access | 2/10 | Wild-card CORS with credentials is critical |
| Database Integrity | 6/10 | Good cascade setup, missing FK relations |
| Code Architecture | 4/10 | Monolith, dead code, naming issues |
| Frontend Correctness | 7/10 | Good routing, minor type safety gaps |
| Performance | 6/10 | N+1 loops, no pagination, large components |

### **Overall Risk Score: `7.5 / 10` (HIGH)**

> **This application should NOT be deployed to production in its current state.** The combination of a brute-forceable authentication system, open CORS, no file validation, and the ability for any user to delete any record represents a high likelihood of data loss or breach with real users.

Addressing the **7 Critical Issues** in Phase 1 would bring the risk score down to approximately **4.5/10 (Moderate)**, which is acceptable for a carefully monitored internal deployment.

